1
00:00:06,149 --> 00:00:13,023
(STAGGERED GROANS)

2
00:00:14,390 --> 00:00:15,658
[ROE2]
UH?

3
00:00:16,159 --> 00:00:17,327
AH, THE SUN...

4
00:00:17,427 --> 00:00:20,763
THE SUN'S
KILLING ME! UGH!

5
00:01:55,425 --> 00:01:58,794
[TOYA] HMMM... IT LOOKS LIKE
WE'VE MADE IT TO ZOOLAND.

6
00:01:58,894 --> 00:02:02,398
[MINORI] UM... WE SHOULD BE ABLE
TO SEE IT PRETTY SOON NOW.

7
00:02:02,498 --> 00:02:03,833
(GASP) THERE IT IS!

8
00:02:03,934 --> 00:02:06,436
UH! OH MY GOD! MT. FUJI!

9
00:02:06,536 --> 00:02:07,837
[ISUZU]
HUH?! WHERE IS IT, TOYA?!

10
00:02:07,938 --> 00:02:10,506
[RUDY]
HMMM, OH THE SACRED MT. FUJI.

11
00:02:10,606 --> 00:02:12,308
[SERARA]
IT'S BIGGER THAN I REMEMBER.

12
00:02:12,408 --> 00:02:15,345
[ISUZU] OMIGOSH! LOOK! THOSE
THINGS TOTALLY LOOK LIKE COWS!

13
00:02:15,445 --> 00:02:17,113
[SERARA] WHAT?!
[MINORI] WAIT. WHERE?

14
00:02:17,213 --> 00:02:19,049
[SERARA] OH, I THINK THAT'S A
HERD OF GREEN ELK

15
00:02:19,149 --> 00:02:20,316
OUT THERE YOU GUYS!

16
00:02:20,416 --> 00:02:21,417
HOW COOL!

17
00:02:21,517 --> 00:02:22,385
[ISUZU]
ARE THEY DANGEROUS?

18
00:02:22,485 --> 00:02:23,553
[SERARA]
WE'LL BE FINE.

19
00:02:23,653 --> 00:02:25,021
NONE OF THEM ARE
CLOSE TO THE ROAD.

20
00:02:25,121 --> 00:02:28,224
AND BESIDES, THEY DON'T
REALLY LOOK FOR TROUBLE.

21
00:02:28,324 --> 00:02:29,659
MOO...

22
00:02:29,759 --> 00:02:31,494
AW, THEY'RE SO CUTE!

23
00:02:31,594 --> 00:02:33,663
THEY REALLY DO
LOOK LIKE COWS.

24
00:02:33,763 --> 00:02:36,899
NOT TO MENTION THEY
MAKE TASTY BARBECUE!

25
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:38,268
[ALL]
EH...?

26
00:02:38,368 --> 00:02:39,769
[SERARA]
MMMM...

27
00:02:46,042 --> 00:02:48,378
[TOYA] (EXHALES) THERE'S
BEEN A LONG SLIGHT CURVE

28
00:02:48,478 --> 00:02:49,913
IN THE ROAD AROUND THESE PARTS.

29
00:02:50,013 --> 00:02:52,515
[MINORI] THAT'S BECAUSE THE ROAD
RUNS AROUND THE SHORELINE.

30
00:02:52,615 --> 00:02:54,117
[TOYA] OH YEAH? THEN
HOW COME ALL I'M SEEING

31
00:02:54,217 --> 00:02:55,751
ARE BUSHES AND TREES?!

32
00:02:55,851 --> 00:02:57,487
[MINORI] (BIG INHALE)
IF YOU TAKE A DEEP BREATH,

33
00:02:57,587 --> 00:02:59,889
YOU CAN SMELL THE OCEAN TOYA.

34
00:03:00,423 --> 00:03:03,193
(SNIFF SNIFF)

35
00:03:03,293 --> 00:03:04,560
[TOYA] NOT GETTING ANYTHING.

36
00:03:04,660 --> 00:03:06,396
WELL EXCEPT FOR
THOSE HORSE BUTTS.

37
00:03:06,496 --> 00:03:07,663
(MINORI GIGGLES)

38
00:03:07,763 --> 00:03:08,932
[TOYA]
NOW IF I REMEMBER RIGHT,

39
00:03:09,032 --> 00:03:11,334
BROTHER SHIROE TOLD
US ABOUT THIS ROAD.

40
00:03:11,434 --> 00:03:12,868
[SHIROE, VOICEOVER]
"THE TOKAIDO"

41
00:03:12,969 --> 00:03:15,605
THAT'S WHAT PEOPLE CALLED
IT A LONG TIME AGO.

42
00:03:15,705 --> 00:03:18,441
IT WAS ONE OF THE ORIGINAL
FIVE ROUTES.

43
00:03:18,541 --> 00:03:20,843
STARTING AT THE NIYONBASHI
BRIDGE IN TOKYO,

44
00:03:20,944 --> 00:03:22,778
IT BECAME A PIVOTAL
POINT OF TRADE.

45
00:03:22,878 --> 00:03:24,180
[TOYA]
UH‐HUH...

46
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:26,416
IN THE REAL WORLD,
THE TOKAIDO ROUTE

47
00:03:26,516 --> 00:03:28,218
IS PRIMARILY USED AS
A MAJOR HIGHWAY.

48
00:03:28,318 --> 00:03:32,622
IT'S CALLED NATIONAL ROUTE ONE.
IT GOES ALL THE WAY INTO OSAKA.

49
00:03:32,722 --> 00:03:33,856
[TOYA]
OSAKA?!

50
00:03:33,957 --> 00:03:36,659
[RUDY]
AH... THE PLACE WE CALL MINAMI.

51
00:03:36,759 --> 00:03:37,994
[MINORI] DOES THAT
MEAN ALL THE ROADS

52
00:03:38,094 --> 00:03:39,829
ARE CONNECTED HERE
AS WELL, SHIROE?

53
00:03:39,930 --> 00:03:42,698
[SHIROE] THAT'S RIGHT... THIS IS
PROBABLY GONNA BE THE FASTEST

54
00:03:42,798 --> 00:03:44,834
WAY THROUGH THE
REDSTONE MOUNTAINS.

55
00:03:44,935 --> 00:03:47,270
[MINORI] MPH.
[TOYA] HM?

56
00:03:47,370 --> 00:03:50,140
IT'S FUNNY. I NEVER REALLY PAID
A WHOLE LOT OF ATTENTION

57
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:52,308
TO THE ROADS BEFORE
WE WOUND UP HERE.

58
00:03:52,408 --> 00:03:55,745
[TOYA] UH... YEAH, I GUESS
I COULD SAY THE SAME THING!

59
00:03:55,845 --> 00:03:58,081
BROTHER SHIROE'S LIKE A
WALKING, TALKING ENCYCLOPEDIA

60
00:03:58,181 --> 00:04:00,083
WITH ALL THE CRAZY
STUFF HE KNOWS!

61
00:04:00,183 --> 00:04:02,485
OH MAN! I'M GONNA LEARN A
WHOLE BUNCH OF STUFF

62
00:04:02,585 --> 00:04:03,987
WHILE WE'RE ON THIS
TRIP, AREN'T I!

63
00:04:04,087 --> 00:04:06,889
(STOMACH GROWLING)
[BOTH] HUH?

64
00:04:06,990 --> 00:04:09,259
MAYBE WE SHOULD WAIT UNTIL
WE'VE HAD LUNCH FIRST!

65
00:04:09,359 --> 00:04:11,427
[ALL]
THAT'S A GREAT IDEA!

66
00:04:12,362 --> 00:04:15,065
[TOYA]
MMM‐MMMMM, YUM!

67
00:04:15,165 --> 00:04:17,767
THE CHIEF MAKES THE BEST HAM
SANDWICHES IN THE UNIVERSE!

68
00:04:17,867 --> 00:04:21,904
[RUDY] MM. YES, HE DOES!
THE MAN IS A MAGICIAN!

69
00:04:22,005 --> 00:04:23,606
[ISUZU]
DON'T EVEN THINK ABOUT IT!

70
00:04:23,706 --> 00:04:25,041
[BOTH]
HUH?

71
00:04:25,141 --> 00:04:27,410
[ISUZU]
NOT EVERYONE HAS HAD THEIRS YET.

72
00:04:27,510 --> 00:04:29,112
[SERARA]
YEAH. YOU HEARD HER!

73
00:04:29,212 --> 00:04:31,982
[SERARA] AH...?
YOU ALMOST BIT MY HAND.

74
00:04:32,082 --> 00:04:34,317
WE SHOULD BE COMING UP ON
CALVET VILLAGE.

75
00:04:34,417 --> 00:04:36,386
YOU WANNA STOP?
... OR GO ON?

76
00:04:36,486 --> 00:04:38,154
WELL, IT'S SUCH
A NICE DAY OUT

77
00:04:38,254 --> 00:04:40,190
I DON'T KNOW WHY WE
CAN'T KEEP ON GOING.

78
00:04:40,290 --> 00:04:42,625
I'M BETTING DANISH AND
CROISSANT CAN DO THIS ALL DAY

79
00:04:42,725 --> 00:04:43,726
IF THEY WANT TO.

80
00:04:43,826 --> 00:04:45,395
(HORSE NEIGHS AND WHINNIES)

81
00:04:45,495 --> 00:04:48,331
[SERARA] YOU HEAR THAT! THEY SAY
THEY CAN GO AS LONG AS WE CAN.

82
00:04:48,431 --> 00:04:49,899
[ISUZU] SOUNDS TO ME LIKE
THEY'RE UP FOR IT.

83
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,734
[SERARA] I KNOW
I CAN KEEP GOING!

84
00:04:51,834 --> 00:04:52,969
[MINORI] YEAH! ME TOO!

85
00:04:53,069 --> 00:04:54,437
[RUDY]
ROADS UNIMAGINED ALWAYS

86
00:04:54,537 --> 00:04:56,672
APPEAR BEFORE RUNDELLHAUS KODE!

87
00:04:56,772 --> 00:04:58,241
[TOYA] ALL RIGHT! WE'D BETTER
GET MOVING

88
00:04:58,341 --> 00:05:00,210
BEFORE IT STARTS
GETTING DARK OUT HERE!

89
00:05:00,310 --> 00:05:01,877
[ALL]
YEAH!

90
00:05:07,918 --> 00:05:10,220
(HORSES WHINNY)
[ALL] WAUUGHHH!

91
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:12,822
(DISORIENTED GROANS)

92
00:05:14,157 --> 00:05:16,559
[TOYA]
OKAY... WHAT WAS THAT ABOUT...?

93
00:05:16,659 --> 00:05:17,860
[ISUZU] WAUUUGHHH!
[ALL] HUH?

94
00:05:17,961 --> 00:05:19,595
[ISUZU]
THEY MUST'VE RUN OUT OF TIME.

95
00:05:19,695 --> 00:05:22,032
THE TWIN HORSE FLUTE
ONLY LASTS A FEW HOURS.

96
00:05:22,132 --> 00:05:24,167
[SERARA]
WELL I GUESS THAT EXPLAINS IT.

97
00:05:24,267 --> 00:05:25,835
THAT'S RIGHT. THEY'RE
ONLY SUPPOSED TO GIVE US

98
00:05:25,936 --> 00:05:27,237
SIX HOURS A DAY.

99
00:05:27,337 --> 00:05:28,871
(DISAPPOINTED)

100
00:05:28,972 --> 00:05:30,573
(LAUGHTER)

101
00:05:30,673 --> 00:05:33,443
WELL I GUESS WE'RE NOT ALL THAT
WORRIED ABOUT IT ARE WE GUYS?

102
00:05:33,543 --> 00:05:35,145
[MINORI]
YEAH, TOTALLY!

103
00:05:35,245 --> 00:05:37,613
YOU HAVE TO ADMIT THAT WAS
STILL A PRETTY QUICK DEPARTURE.

104
00:05:37,713 --> 00:05:40,816
I MEAN SERIOUSLY, WHY DIDN'T
THOSE TWO MOVE THAT FAST BEFORE.

105
00:05:40,917 --> 00:05:42,318
[RUDY]
GOOD QUESTION!

106
00:05:42,418 --> 00:05:43,753
THAT IS JUST RUDE,

107
00:05:43,853 --> 00:05:46,089
AND AFTER THEY ATE CARROTS
RIGHT OUTTA MY HANDS!

108
00:05:46,189 --> 00:05:47,790
[ISUZU] NOT TO MENTION THE
CABBAGE! [RUDY] HUH...?

109
00:05:47,890 --> 00:05:50,360
THEY DON'T HAVE A SINGLE
SHRED OF HUMAN DECENCY!

110
00:05:50,460 --> 00:05:51,694
THAT'S BECAUSE THEY'RE HORSES.

111
00:05:51,794 --> 00:05:53,696
WELL THAT'S NO EXCUSE...

112
00:05:53,796 --> 00:05:56,432
YOU KNOW... EVEN
HORSES SHOULD KNOW

113
00:05:56,532 --> 00:05:58,268
IT'S NOT RIGHT TO EAT AND RUN.

114
00:05:58,368 --> 00:06:01,804
(LAUGHTER)

115
00:06:01,904 --> 00:06:03,406
[RUDY] OKAY, WE LOST THE HORSES.

116
00:06:03,506 --> 00:06:05,808
BUT THAT JUST GIVES US
ANOTHER ADVENTURE, RIGHT?

117
00:06:05,908 --> 00:06:09,579
[TOYA] YOU BET...!
SO WHERE ARE WE, ANYWAY?

118
00:06:09,679 --> 00:06:11,081
[MINORI] WELL WITH TRAVEL TIME,

119
00:06:11,181 --> 00:06:13,716
WE'RE SOMEWHERE BETWEEN
CALVET AND WILLISTORIA.

120
00:06:13,816 --> 00:06:15,651
[ISUZU] WE'RE NOT GONNA GET
ANYWHERE VERY FAST

121
00:06:15,751 --> 00:06:17,153
WITHOUT A SET OF FRESH HORSES.

122
00:06:17,253 --> 00:06:18,554
(DEFLATED)

123
00:06:19,789 --> 00:06:21,257
GUESS THIS MEANS
WE'RE CAMPING TONIGHT!

124
00:06:21,357 --> 00:06:23,293
WELL I DON'T SEE A
HOTEL OR ANYTHING.

125
00:06:23,393 --> 00:06:26,096
JUST AS LONG AS EVERYONE
LEAVES THE COOKING TO ME.

126
00:06:26,196 --> 00:06:28,764
NOW THIS IS WHERE ADVENTURERS
ARE AT THEIR BEST!

127
00:06:28,864 --> 00:06:31,101
WE'RE NOT ALL
OUTDOORSMEN, YOU KNOW?

128
00:06:31,201 --> 00:06:32,936
[BOYS]
LET'S PITCH CAMP!

129
00:06:33,036 --> 00:06:35,005
[GIRLS]
YEAH!

130
00:06:42,645 --> 00:06:45,315
[RUDY] HMM. HEH.
(CLAPPING)

131
00:06:45,415 --> 00:06:46,482
[TOYA]
PERFECT.

132
00:06:46,582 --> 00:06:47,750
[BOTH]
WAUUUGHHHH!

133
00:06:47,850 --> 00:06:52,055
(HAPPY SOUNDS)

134
00:06:52,655 --> 00:06:55,125
(HUMS A TUNE)

135
00:06:55,225 --> 00:06:56,192
(SURPRISED)

136
00:06:58,929 --> 00:07:01,932
[ALL] THANK YOU FOR THE FOOD!
(EATING)

137
00:07:02,032 --> 00:07:03,934
[TOYA] IT'S REALLY... GOOD.
[SERARA] HM?

138
00:07:04,034 --> 00:07:06,169
[MINORI] OH YEAH, THIS
IS, DEFINITELY GOOD.

139
00:07:06,269 --> 00:07:08,004
[ISUZU]
IT'S JUST... A LITTLE...

140
00:07:08,104 --> 00:07:10,740
[RUDY]
IT'S REALLY BLAND... AND BITTER

141
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:11,774
[ISUZU]
RUDY!

142
00:07:11,874 --> 00:07:13,143
(GASP AND SCREAM)

143
00:07:13,243 --> 00:07:15,245
[SERARA]
I'M SORRY! I'M SORRY! I'M SORRY!

144
00:07:15,345 --> 00:07:17,280
[SERARA] WHENEVER I'M
COOKING WITH CHIEF NYANTA,

145
00:07:17,380 --> 00:07:19,782
IT ALWAYS COMES OUT THE
WAY IT'S SUPPOSED TO...

146
00:07:19,882 --> 00:07:21,017
[TOYA] HEY, THE
MORE YOU DO IT,

147
00:07:21,117 --> 00:07:22,652
THE BETTER YOU'LL GET!
DON'T SWEAT IT!

148
00:07:22,752 --> 00:07:24,520
IF THE CHIEF WERE
HERE RIGHT NOW...

149
00:07:24,620 --> 00:07:28,858
HE'D TELL YOU TO TAKE IT EASY,
BABY. YOU CAN TOTALLY DO IT!

150
00:07:28,959 --> 00:07:31,261
[RUDY] KEEP WORKING TO
IMPROVE, YOU'LL BE FINE.

151
00:07:31,361 --> 00:07:33,429
[MINORI] I WISH MORE OF US
HAD THE COOKING SKILL,

152
00:07:33,529 --> 00:07:34,864
SO WE COULD ALL HELP COOK!

153
00:07:34,965 --> 00:07:36,699
[ISUZU] SORRY WE'RE
COUNTING ON YOU

154
00:07:36,799 --> 00:07:38,268
FOR ALL THE GRUB,
LITTLE DUDE‐ETTE!

155
00:07:38,368 --> 00:07:40,436
(INHALE) YOU'RE
ABSOLUTELY RIGHT!

156
00:07:40,536 --> 00:07:43,073
I'VE GOTTA KEEP TRYING FOR
EVERYONE IN MY GUILD!

157
00:07:43,173 --> 00:07:45,741
[SERARA] I'M THE ONE WEARING
THE NEWLYWED WIFE'S APRON!

158
00:07:45,841 --> 00:07:49,779
IT'S TIME I LIVE UP TO CHIEF
NYANTA'S LEGACY OF AMAZING FOOD!

159
00:07:49,879 --> 00:07:51,481
(CHEERS)

160
00:07:51,581 --> 00:07:53,116
(STRUMMING LUTE)

161
00:07:54,985 --> 00:07:56,552
[MINORI] SO IT LOOKS LIKE THE
NEXT BEST PLACE

162
00:07:56,652 --> 00:07:58,254
TO STOP IS SAZAN VILLAGE.

163
00:07:58,354 --> 00:08:00,223
[TOYA] HOW LONG WILL
IT TAKE TO GET THERE?

164
00:08:00,323 --> 00:08:01,724
WELL IF WE CAN'T
GET MORE THAN

165
00:08:01,824 --> 00:08:03,226
SIX HOURS A DAY
OUT OF THE HORSES...

166
00:08:03,326 --> 00:08:05,528
IT'S PROBABLY GONNA TAKE
US ANOTHER THREE DAYS.

167
00:08:05,628 --> 00:08:07,797
AHHH! WHY IN THE HECK ARE WE
RUNNING INTO ALL THIS TROUBLE

168
00:08:07,897 --> 00:08:09,332
ON OUR FIRST JOURNEY?

169
00:08:09,432 --> 00:08:12,602
WHY CAN'T IT BE A NORMAL
ADVENTURE LIKE IT USED TO BE?

170
00:08:12,702 --> 00:08:14,104
S'NOT SO BAD...

171
00:08:14,204 --> 00:08:16,372
WE'VE GOT OUR GUILDMATES WITH
US KEEPING US COMPANY...

172
00:08:16,472 --> 00:08:18,841
IT KINDA MAKES THE WHOLE
THING MORE FUN, Y'KNOW.

173
00:08:18,942 --> 00:08:20,443
I'M SURE THAT'S WHY SHIROE AND

174
00:08:20,543 --> 00:08:22,445
THE OTHERS SENT US
IN THE FIRST PLACE

175
00:08:22,545 --> 00:08:25,848
TO TEACH US TO TAKE CARE OF EACH
OTHER. AND TO TRUST EACH OTHER.

176
00:08:25,949 --> 00:08:28,718
HMPH. LOOK AT
YOU, MINORI.

177
00:08:28,818 --> 00:08:30,386
HUH?

178
00:08:30,486 --> 00:08:32,522
IT SURE IS STRANGE
TO SEE MY BIG SISTER

179
00:08:32,622 --> 00:08:34,490
ALL GROWN UP LIKE THIS.

180
00:08:40,997 --> 00:08:43,533
MM? ALL GROWN UP?

181
00:08:43,633 --> 00:08:45,501
I KINDA ALWAYS THOUGHT YOU
AND I WERE GONNA GROW UP AT

182
00:08:45,601 --> 00:08:49,272
THE SAME SPEED. BUT YOU'RE
MOVING PRETTY FAST.

183
00:08:49,372 --> 00:08:51,041
[MINORI]
YOU'RE EXAGGERATING.

184
00:08:51,141 --> 00:08:52,808
WHICH ONE OF US WAS STRONGER
WHEN THIS APOCALYPSE

185
00:08:52,908 --> 00:08:54,677
MESS GOT STARTED?

186
00:08:54,777 --> 00:08:57,880
HEH. THERE'S NO WAY I WOULD HAVE
GOTTEN THIS FAR IF I DIDN'T

187
00:08:57,981 --> 00:09:00,316
HAVE YOU HERE TO HELP
ME THROUGH ALL THIS.

188
00:09:00,416 --> 00:09:03,019
WELL, I AM YOUR BIG
BROTHER YOU KNOW.

189
00:09:03,119 --> 00:09:05,321
HUH? UH... I'M
THE BIG SISTER HERE

190
00:09:05,421 --> 00:09:06,789
[TOYA]
NO, I'M DEFINITELY OLDER!

191
00:09:06,889 --> 00:09:08,191
[MINORI]
YOU HAVE LOST YOUR MIND.

192
00:09:08,291 --> 00:09:10,193
[TOYA] NO, I AM! I'M
EVEN TALLER THAN YOU ARE!

193
00:09:10,293 --> 00:09:11,962
[MINORI] OH WHATEVER. THAT
DOESN'T MEAN ANYTHING.

194
00:09:12,062 --> 00:09:13,496
[TOYA]
UH, IT SURE DOES!

195
00:09:15,765 --> 00:09:18,401
[MARIELLE] THE KIDS LEFT FOR
THEIR EXPEDITION THREE DAYS AGO.

196
00:09:18,501 --> 00:09:22,572
AWW... I HOPE THEY'RE
NOT GETTING HOMESICK...

197
00:09:22,672 --> 00:09:24,007
[HENRIETTA] I DOUBT IT!

198
00:09:24,107 --> 00:09:26,209
I BET THEY'RE ROMPING ABOUT
LIKE IT'S A SCHOOL TRIP.

199
00:09:26,309 --> 00:09:27,877
THEY MIGHT EVEN START TELLING
THEMSELVES

200
00:09:27,978 --> 00:09:29,412
THEY DON'T WANT TO COME BACK!

201
00:09:29,512 --> 00:09:32,482
[AKATSUKI] HMN... THAT WOULDN'T
BE GOOD EITHER, WOULD IT?

202
00:09:32,582 --> 00:09:33,549
(SIGH)

203
00:09:34,584 --> 00:09:36,886
[HENRIETTA] YOU'RE LOOKING
PALE AGAIN, RIEZE.

204
00:09:36,987 --> 00:09:38,654
HUH? I'M ALL RIGHT,
IT'S NOTHING.

205
00:09:38,754 --> 00:09:42,625
HM‐MM. YOUR EYES ARE STARTING
TO LOOK STERN, LIKE MY LORD.

206
00:09:42,725 --> 00:09:45,195
INTENSE AND SEVERE.
HUH?

207
00:09:45,295 --> 00:09:48,231
YOU DON'T NEED TO PUSH YOURSELF
AS HARD AS YOU HAVE BEEN.

208
00:09:48,331 --> 00:09:50,000
[RIEZE]
OKAY...

209
00:09:50,100 --> 00:09:53,036
THE ABSENCE OF KRUSTY MUST
BE TAKING ITS TOLL ON YOU.

210
00:09:53,136 --> 00:09:54,804
THAT'S TRUE, IT'S BEEN
DIFFICULT.

211
00:09:54,904 --> 00:09:57,673
WORKING WITHOUT HIM OR TAKAYAMA
HAS BEEN VERY HARD FOR ME.

212
00:09:57,773 --> 00:10:00,276
D. D. D. IS STILL FUNCTIONING
PROPERLY FOR NOW,

213
00:10:00,376 --> 00:10:03,546
BUT THERE ARE A LOT OF UNKNOWN
FACTORS FACING US AT THE MOMENT.

214
